{
  "name": "OneFlare DNS-Tunnel / C2 Beaconing Response (CF-Gateway-DNSTunnel)",
  "description": "Fires on the SentinelOne scheduled detection CF-Gateway-DNSTunnel (Cloudflare Gateway DNS, OCSF class_uid 4003, rule 2519102258169184569). Extracts the C2 base-domain (zone), source IP/device and beacon context from the alert, then runs two enrichments: (a) an S1 SDL PowerQuery for the same src_ip's other DNS beaconing in a 6h window (sustained tunnel vs one-off blip) and (b) a VirusTotal DOMAIN reputation lookup on the base-domain (domain, not just IP, is the load-bearing indicator for DNS C2). A decision branch gates containment on domain reputation OR beacon persistence. Containment: a Cloudflare Gateway DNS policy that blocks the base-domain (native DNS-tunnel containment), a zone IP Access rule on the source IP, S1 DNS+IPV4 IOCs, an S1 alert note (base domain, query volume, entropy, beacon persistence, reputation), an alert-verdict raise to SUSPICIOUS, and Slack+email notification. Endpoint isolation is an optional escalation gated on the alert binding to a real EDR asset (device_uid). run_automatically is false so an analyst approves from the Singularity Response console. MITRE T1071.004 / T1048 / T1568.002.",
